WEBVTT

1
00:02:33.202 --> 00:02:35.670
They didn't hurt you. did they?

2
00:02:41.544 --> 00:02:43.444
Calm down.

3
00:02:44.547 --> 00:02:46.674
It's all over.

4
00:02:54.323 --> 00:02:57.656
What's your name?

5
00:02:57.760 --> 00:02:59.159
Gloria.

6
00:03:00.863 --> 00:03:05.926
Well. Gloria. you're all right.
They're gone. Calm down.

7
00:03:10.473 --> 00:03:13.374
- And you. what's your name?
- Enrique.

8
00:03:35.398 --> 00:03:38.128
Thank you. Enrique.

9
00:03:54.951 --> 00:03:56.282
Extra! Extra!
The latest news!

10
00:03:58.387 --> 00:04:01.083
Fidel Castro
and all those with him...

11
00:04:01.190 --> 00:04:05.092
were killed in
the Oriente province!

12
00:04:05.194 --> 00:04:09.756
The latest news!
The latest news!

13
00:04:09.866 --> 00:04:12.562
Fidel Castro dead!

14
00:04:21.811 --> 00:04:24.279
Stop at the university.

15
00:05:01.017 --> 00:05:04.783
- They killed Fidel Castro.
- It's not true.

16
00:05:04.887 --> 00:05:08.550
- Here. It's in the paper.
- It's not true.

17
00:05:08.658 --> 00:05:11.388
Where's Alberto?

18
00:05:12.495 --> 00:05:16.522
Alberto. Fidel Castro
has been killed!

19
00:05:16.632 --> 00:05:19.601
It's a lie. Enrique.
Here's what we need to do.

20
00:05:19.702 --> 00:05:24.036
We have to let all Havana
know that this is a lie.

21
00:05:24.140 --> 00:05:26.938
Fidel Castro is alive.

22
00:05:27.043 --> 00:05:30.240
He and his comrades...

23
00:05:30.346 --> 00:05:33.406
have landed
in the Oriente province.

24
00:05:33.516 --> 00:05:35.279
Careful.

25
00:05:38.120 --> 00:05:41.647
And have begun the struggle.

26
00:05:41.757 --> 00:05:44.123
Write this down.

27
00:05:44.226 --> 00:05:48.060
Batista is spreading
the rumor...

28
00:05:48.164 --> 00:05:51.895
that Fidel is dead to divert
the people from their goal.

29
00:05:53.135 --> 00:05:56.798
Fidel is in the Sierra Maestra.

30
00:05:56.906 --> 00:06:01.673
He's gathering all honest people
under the banner of the revolution.

31
00:06:01.777 --> 00:06:06.373
Read this. They've killed
Juan. Carlos and Luis.

32
00:06:06.482 --> 00:06:09.576
Are we just going to go on sitting
here with our hands folded?

33
00:06:09.685 --> 00:06:14.782
That fat murderer is going
to keep killing our comrades.

34
00:06:14.890 --> 00:06:18.053
We're ready.
but this is not appropriate.

35
00:06:18.160 --> 00:06:21.061
So we kill this one. but in
his place. they'll put another.

36
00:06:21.163 --> 00:06:23.791
We'll kill that one too.

37
00:06:23.899 --> 00:06:26.424
So that's how we're going
to spend the rest of our lives?

38
00:06:26.535 --> 00:06:29.095
But he killed Juan.
Luis and Carlos.

39
00:06:29.205 --> 00:06:32.663
What are we going to accomplish
by killing one man?

40
00:06:32.775 --> 00:06:35.903
They'll just put another one
in his place. only much harsher.

41
00:06:36.012 --> 00:06:38.412
And he'll keep on killing
our comrades.

42
00:06:38.514 --> 00:06:40.914
You cannot confuse people.
or one man. with a system.

43
00:06:41.017 --> 00:06:43.508
But people make the system.

44
00:06:43.619 --> 00:06:48.147
True. but we have to struggle
against the system. not the people.

45
00:06:48.257 --> 00:06:52.353
I understand. but this is not
a human being. He's a murderer!

46
00:06:52.461 --> 00:06:55.328
He's killing our comrades.

47
00:06:55.431 --> 00:06:59.094
Don't you think
I want to kill him too?

48
00:06:59.201 --> 00:07:02.534
But they have landed successfully.

49
00:07:02.638 --> 00:07:06.768
Fidel is alive. There is a new
struggle developing there...

50
00:07:06.876 --> 00:07:10.505
and we must assist that effort.

51
00:07:10.613 --> 00:07:12.774
The people have to know everything!

52
00:07:12.882 --> 00:07:16.613
I know. but what we do with
this murderer is just as important.

53
00:07:16.719 --> 00:07:20.280
We can't decide on that now.
We'll discuss this later. Later.

54
00:07:20.389 --> 00:07:22.755
When? When?

55
00:07:22.858 --> 00:07:28.091
If you want. raise the question
at the group meeting.

56
00:07:28.197 --> 00:07:33.066
Alberto. they killed Pepe
last night.

57
00:07:46.148 --> 00:07:48.844
And what are we going
to do about it?

58
00:07:48.951 --> 00:07:53.081
I have already told you.
We'll discuss this later.

59
00:08:09.805 --> 00:08:12.069
The forgiveness

60
00:08:12.174 --> 00:08:15.041
You sing my song

61
00:08:15.144 --> 00:08:18.307
With such melody. it tries

62
00:08:18.414 --> 00:08:25.820
To get me to forget
your betrayal

63
00:08:45.774 --> 00:08:49.835
You want to come back

64
00:08:49.945 --> 00:08:53.574
Perhaps you think of me
Perhaps you cry for me

65
00:08:53.682 --> 00:08:56.150
Perhaps. but is that really you

66
00:08:56.252 --> 00:08:58.880
Now you beg for forgiveness

67
00:08:58.988 --> 00:09:01.252
And you sing your song

68
00:09:01.357 --> 00:09:03.552
With such melody. it tries

69
00:09:03.659 --> 00:09:09.291
To get me to forget
your betrayal

70
00:09:11.600 --> 00:09:14.330
But now. don't you understand

71
00:09:14.436 --> 00:09:17.735
That it's taken you
too long to come back

72
00:09:17.840 --> 00:09:22.868
And I cannot forget
that you made me cry

73
00:09:22.978 --> 00:09:26.414
I won't be able to forgive you

74
00:15:48.697 --> 00:15:52.292
What's the matter with you?
Can't you see where you're going?

75
00:15:52.401 --> 00:15:56.394
You're nuts! Are you crazy?
Are you asleep?

76
00:15:56.505 --> 00:16:01.841
You were right under my wheels.
you maniac. Imbecile!

77
00:16:01.944 --> 00:16:05.539
- Are you drunk? Answer me!
- What's wrong?

78
00:16:05.647 --> 00:16:10.175
This guy almost got me put in jail.
What is he. crazy?

79
00:16:18.527 --> 00:16:23.396
Be careful. Enrique. Watch out when
you're in the middle of the street.

80
00:16:30.872 --> 00:16:33.670
Where to. Enrique?

81
00:16:39.114 --> 00:16:43.483
What's up? What's the matter?

82
00:16:45.754 --> 00:16:48.484
Enrique. what's going on?

83
00:16:48.590 --> 00:16:53.994
I couldn't-- He was having
fried eggs for breakfast.

84
00:16:54.096 --> 00:16:59.159
Fried eggs? What are you
talking about. Enrique?

85
00:16:59.267 --> 00:17:04.068
He was with his kids.
I couldn't--

86
00:17:59.995 --> 00:18:04.329
Did you consider
the consequences?

87
00:18:16.278 --> 00:18:21.944
Who gave you permission
to do this? Who?

88
00:18:22.050 --> 00:18:23.950
Shit!

89
00:20:02.217 --> 00:20:04.208
Open up!

90
00:20:05.320 --> 00:20:08.346
Everybody stay where you are!

91
00:20:10.859 --> 00:20:13.054
Search them!

92
00:20:45.126 --> 00:20:48.220
Whose book is this?

93
00:21:01.776 --> 00:21:03.903
Yours?

94
00:21:14.089 --> 00:21:16.614
Who does this book belong to?

95
00:21:17.759 --> 00:21:21.752
"Lenin. The State and Revolution."

96
00:21:23.632 --> 00:21:27.124
- Whose book is this?
- It's ours.

97
00:21:27.235 --> 00:21:30.671
- Yours?
- It's our book.

98
00:21:30.772 --> 00:21:36.506
And anybody who hasn't read it
is an ignoramus.

99
00:21:40.215 --> 00:21:43.582
Long live freedom!
Long live the revolution!

100
00:21:43.685 --> 00:21:46.313
Cubans! Fidel lives!

101
00:21:46.421 --> 00:21:49.515
He's up in the Sierra Maestra
with his comrades.

102
00:21:49.624 --> 00:21:52.957
He and his comrades
are fighting against Batista.

103
00:23:00.095 --> 00:23:05.294
Long live liberty!
Death to the tyrant!

104
00:23:05.400 --> 00:23:09.962
Long live liberty!
Down with tyranny!

105
00:23:13.074 --> 00:23:16.373
Liberty or death!

106
00:24:52.440 --> 00:24:57.275
I am Cuba.

107
00:24:57.378 --> 00:25:03.442
There are two paths for people
when they are born.

108
00:25:03.551 --> 00:25:08.420
The path of slavery--
it crushes and decays.

109
00:25:08.523 --> 00:25:13.187
And the path of the star--
it illuminates. but kills.

110
00:25:13.294 --> 00:25:16.855
These are the words
of José Marti.

111
00:25:16.965 --> 00:25:19.798
You will choose the star.

112
00:25:19.901 --> 00:25:24.065
Your path will be hard.
and it will be marked by blood.

113
00:25:24.172 --> 00:25:28.541
But in the name of justice.
wherever a single person goes...

114
00:25:28.643 --> 00:25:31.134
thousands more will rise up.

115
00:25:31.246 --> 00:25:38.812
And when there are no more people.
then the stones will rise up.

116
00:25:38.920 --> 00:25:41.787
I am Cuba.

117
00:25:43.391 --> 00:25:48.590
When men are born.
there are two paths.

118
00:25:49.831 --> 00:25:52.527
You will choose the star.

119
00:25:57.172 --> 00:25:59.697
The path will be hard...

120
00:26:02.944 --> 00:26:06.141
and it will be marked by blood.

121
00:26:11.286 --> 00:26:16.553
For the last time.
clear the steps. It's an order!

122
00:29:22.343 --> 00:29:26.973
Come on. guys!
Over here behind the cars!

123
00:30:29.944 --> 00:30:33.937
Enrique! Enrique!

124
00:39:46.233 --> 00:39:49.600
Where is Fidel?

125
00:39:49.703 --> 00:39:53.036
Fidel? I am Fidel.

126
00:39:53.140 --> 00:39:57.372
- Where is Fidel?
- I am Fidel!

127
00:39:59.279 --> 00:40:01.873
I am Fidel.

128
00:40:25.706 --> 00:40:29.904
I am Cuba.

129
00:40:30.010 --> 00:40:36.677
These are the people
about whom legends will be told.

130
00:40:36.784 --> 00:40:41.585
From all parts. they're coming to
the mountains of the Sierra Maestra.

131
00:40:41.688 --> 00:40:45.283
They are going to fight
for liberty.

132
00:45:24.137 --> 00:45:27.265
Come in. Have a seat.

133
00:45:48.428 --> 00:45:51.829
Amelia. bring another plate.

134
00:47:09.409 --> 00:47:13.243
Do you need the rifle too?

135
00:47:19.953 --> 00:47:21.443
No.

136
00:47:28.495 --> 00:47:31.931
These hands aren't for killing.

137
00:47:32.032 --> 00:47:34.933
They're for sowing.

138
00:47:41.875 --> 00:47:46.437
But is this land
you are sowing yours?

139
00:48:02.896 --> 00:48:04.796
Have you finished?

140
00:48:21.581 --> 00:48:25.642
Don't you wish there
were a school on your land?

141
00:48:28.688 --> 00:48:31.748
Shoes for your kids?

142
00:48:32.926 --> 00:48:36.885
That when they are sick.
they would receive treatment?

143
00:48:38.331 --> 00:48:41.596
Or are they going to live
the way you do?

144
00:48:52.879 --> 00:48:55.848
I want to live in peace.

145
00:48:58.718 --> 00:49:00.117
Me too.

146
00:49:07.827 --> 00:49:10.455
What about this. then?

147
00:49:12.032 --> 00:49:14.466
So as to live in peace.

148
00:49:17.337 --> 00:49:18.736
Get out!

149
00:50:00.113 --> 00:50:06.643
He's exhausted. Mariano.
Let him stay the night.

150
00:51:31.475 --> 00:51:35.036
Do you hear that. Mariano?

151
00:51:35.145 --> 00:51:37.978
They're bombing the mountains.

152
00:52:39.710 --> 00:52:41.575
Amelia. don't go!

153
00:52:41.678 --> 00:52:45.808
Amelia. calm down.
Amelia. calm down.

154
00:53:27.925 --> 00:53:30.689
Listen. Mariano. listen!

155
00:53:30.794 --> 00:53:33.524
Amelia. wait! Wait!

156
00:53:33.630 --> 00:53:37.532
Amelia! Calm down. dear.

157
00:53:42.873 --> 00:53:44.272
Amelia!

158
00:54:31.555 --> 00:54:37.255
Mariano. my child!

159
00:54:37.361 --> 00:54:40.922
Mariano!

160
00:54:52.376 --> 00:54:53.934
Amelia!

161
01:00:33.984 --> 01:00:36.612
I have to go. Amelia.

162
01:01:00.777 --> 01:01:03.211
I have to go.

163
01:01:43.586 --> 01:01:45.486
Halt!

164
01:01:53.163 --> 01:01:56.599
This is the Insurgent Radio...

165
01:01:56.700 --> 01:01:59.863
broadcasting
from the Oriente province.

166
01:01:59.969 --> 01:02:04.872
From Sierra Maestra.
Free Territory of Cuba.

167
01:02:20.123 --> 01:02:25.117
Cubans. join the struggle.

168
01:02:25.228 --> 01:02:31.565
You. victim of humiliation.
hatred and crime.

169
01:02:31.668 --> 01:02:36.867
You have borne on your shoulders
injustice...

170
01:02:36.973 --> 01:02:40.704
destitution and the deprivation
of your rights.

171
01:02:40.810 --> 01:02:43.472
Listen!

172
01:02:43.580 --> 01:02:48.574
Revolution! Revolution!

173
01:02:48.685 --> 01:02:54.419
In the face of hostile malice.
you. peasant;

174
01:02:54.524 --> 01:02:59.188
you. worker; you. student;

175
01:02:59.295 --> 01:03:01.195
you. Cuban!

176
01:03:01.297 --> 01:03:04.664
Raise your armed fist!

177
01:03:04.768 --> 01:03:09.762
The revolution is fighting
for the complete and absolute...

178
01:03:09.873 --> 01:03:12.740
national independence
of our motherland.

179
01:03:12.842 --> 01:03:15.777
The revolution fights...

180
01:03:15.879 --> 01:03:19.679
so that the people
may own their own land.

181
01:03:19.783 --> 01:03:23.150
For education that is not
just a privilege for the rich.

182
01:03:24.788 --> 01:03:30.021
We fight for the defense of life...

183
01:03:30.126 --> 01:03:34.563
given to each of us.

184
01:03:34.664 --> 01:03:37.292
Each family has the right...

185
01:03:37.400 --> 01:03:39.459
to adequate housing.

186
01:03:39.569 --> 01:03:43.972
Each Cuban has the right to work.

187
01:03:44.073 --> 01:03:49.636
Thousands of heads of families and
thousands of young people have no work.

188
01:03:49.746 --> 01:03:51.646
They have no future.

189
01:03:51.748 --> 01:03:55.878
The revolution
will industrialize the country.

190
01:03:55.985 --> 01:04:02.481
It will eliminate unemployment
and will restore to the people...

191
01:04:04.561 --> 01:04:07.496
all the wealth
that was stolen from them.

192
01:04:07.597 --> 01:04:10.293
You. farmer. You. worker.

193
01:04:10.400 --> 01:04:13.130
You. student.

194
01:04:13.236 --> 01:04:16.205
Take your place in the struggle.

195
01:04:16.306 --> 01:04:19.867
This is your revolution!

196
01:04:19.976 --> 01:04:23.002
Liberty or death!

197
01:04:57.080 --> 01:05:00.982
I knew you would come.

198
01:05:01.084 --> 01:05:02.984
I knew it.

199
01:05:05.321 --> 01:05:08.882
Now I need a rifle.

200
01:05:08.992 --> 01:05:11.790
A rifle?

201
01:05:11.895 --> 01:05:15.626
This guy thinks
they grow on trees!

202
01:05:15.732 --> 01:05:19.793
Plant some.
Maybe more will grow.

203
01:05:27.010 --> 01:05:29.137
Look. Mariano.

204
01:05:32.415 --> 01:05:37.580
You have to capture a rifle
in battle.

205
01:05:37.687 --> 01:05:40.986
Every one of us
has done it that way.

206
01:06:41.417 --> 01:06:47.049
I am Cuba.

207
01:06:47.156 --> 01:06:51.991
Your hands have gotten
used to farming tools.

208
01:06:53.730 --> 01:06:57.791
But now a rifle is in your hands.

209
01:06:59.235 --> 01:07:04.298
You are not shooting to kill.

210
01:07:04.407 --> 01:07:08.343
You are firing at the past.

211
01:07:10.213 --> 01:07:15.515
You are firing
to protect your future.

212
01:07:54.557 --> 01:07:59.426
Run to the battle
fellow people of Bayamo

213
01:07:59.529 --> 01:08:03.829
Your country looks at you
with pride

214
01:08:03.933 --> 01:08:08.233
Do not fear a glorious death

215
01:08:08.337 --> 01:08:12.296
To die for your motherland
is to live

216
01:08:13.409 --> 01:08:17.175
To live enchained is to submit

217
01:08:17.280 --> 01:08:22.217
To insult and ignominy

218
01:08:22.318 --> 01:08:26.084
Hear the bugle sound

219
01:08:27.523 --> 01:08:35.931
Prepare for battle. O valiant ones
Onward

220
01:09:52.008 --> 01:10:00.643
The End

221
01:10:38.120 --> 01:10:41.021
Subtitles By
Captions. Inc. Los Angeles
